### File Location
`src/format/markdown.rs`

### CRITICAL: Mode Behavior
Markdown rendering ONLY in Rich mode. Other modes:
- Plain: Strip markdown, output raw text
- JSON: Return raw markdown string unchanged
- Quiet: No output

### rich_rust Markdown Component
```rust
use rich_rust::markdown::Markdown;
use crate::format::OutputContext;

pub fn render_markdown(content: &str, ctx: &OutputContext) -> String {
    if !ctx.is_rich() {
        // Strip markdown for plain/json mode
        return strip_markdown(content);
    }

    let md = Markdown::new(content)
        .with_code_theme("monokai")
        .with_hyperlinks(true)
        .with_width(ctx.width());

    md.render()
}
```

### Supported Elements
- **Bold** and *italic* text
- `inline code`
- Code blocks (with syntax highlighting - see beads_rust-1jcq)
- Lists (ordered and unordered)
- Headers (scale down for embedding)
- Links (clickable in supported terminals)
- Blockquotes
- Horizontal rules

### Integration Points
Markdown rendering used by:
- IssuePanel description section
